</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufeltrakfizzlefingers.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feltrak Fizzlefingers</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/26/01 11:37:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ROFL</span><hr size=1> The old strategy was to /q after hitting numlock and running through the corridors. You had 3 seconds to get a direction and hit /q. But now that they fixed the velious faction bug thing that made them delay before killing you, you can't stay alive long enough to get the direction and hit /q. <br>
Strategy 2: Just like a fear crack. This however, requires more luck. The easiest way , if you have smart people, is to have each try to run as far as they can toward PoM. Let them die. Get a necro and have him run for the 'safe spot.' If he is skilled and gets some luck with him, he can FD there and /q. May take a few tries. Necro logs to an alt. Now is the monks and rogue's turns. They both pull all the corpses that didn't make it far enough, to the safe spot. Necro res's an epic cleric, and the epic cleric starts the resing, but make sure they aren't pulling more corpses here =D Res everyone in, then the hard part is next. (Yep, that was the easy part) The raid must now kill a few dragons, one fight including two dragons at once. These are level 60 dragons I believe but one CH's and the other is like Wuoshi. Kill these 2 and a level 65 (I think) dragon and you can safely go to PoM. As you may have realized, you have to get a raid to do it. BUT, you could try running 2 groups there, and pray that at least 1 cleric makes it in, and have a necro summon the other's corpses. If you get a few people in there, the unicorn would be cake.<br>
